keyPredicate

public ReducingSubmittableJob<EntryKey,Key,Value> keyPredicate(KeyPredicate<EntryKey> predicate)
Description copied from interface: ReducingSubmittableJob
Defines the KeyPredicate implementation to preselect keys the MapReduce task will be executed on. Preselecting keys can speed up the job massively.
This method can be used in conjunction with ReducingSubmittableJob.onKeys(Iterable) or ReducingSubmittableJob.onKeys(Object...) to define a range of known and evaluated keys.

Specified by:
keyPredicate in interface ReducingSubmittableJob<EntryKey,Key,Value>
Parameters:
predicate - predicate implementation to be used to evaluate keys
Returns:
instance of this Job with generics changed on usage

chunkSize

public ReducingSubmittableJob<EntryKey,Key,Value> chunkSize(int chunkSize)
Description copied from interface: ReducingSubmittableJob
Defines the number of elements per chunk. Whenever the chunk size is reached and a ReducerFactory is defined the chunk will be send to the nodes that is responsible for the emitted keys.
Please note, that chunks are deactivated when no ReducerFactory is defined

Specified by:
chunkSize in interface ReducingSubmittableJob<EntryKey,Key,Value>
